The paper deals with graph drawing, specifically orthogonal drawings, which falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of canonical order and the fact that the graph is 3-connected suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The optimization of area suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of graph theory (cs.GT) and computational complexity (cs.SI).
